@FDSeoul:
If some one is "leeching", that is someone who is downloading and seeding at the same time. A seeder has finished downloading and is just seeding, not seeding the same file one is downloading. SO, ASSHOLE, If you are downloading and are seeding you are telling yourself to fuck off. To NOT BE A LEECHER, or TO BE a "SEEDER", you must have the file 100% downloaded, and then be in the act of uploading it at that time. If you haven't finished downloading but have started seeding, as I pointed out, you are a LEECHER by definition.  Wikipedia explains this in detail to any and all who think I am wrong. The term "leeching" is misleading.

You can download and turn your uploading amount to ZERO kb per sec, that makes you a "leecher" too I think there should be a separate term for that called "Douching". 
It actually doesn't negatively affect your download speed by uploading at the same time.
The term leeching was coined early in bit torrent software development several many years back and really is too negative sounding for what it actually means.
I think it is very infrequent for people to not upload at least a little while downloading. That shouldn't be called a negative term but yet it is.
